TITLE      Study of the uncertainty quantification of the
            121Sb(n,g)122Sb reaction
AUTHOR     (N.Singh, M.Choudhary, A.Gandhi, M.Upadhyay,
            R.K.Singh, A.Hingu, G.Mishra, S.De, L.S.Danu, A.Kumar,
            R.G.Thomas, S.Sood, S.Prasad, B.Lalremruata,
            K.Katovsky, A.Kumar)
INSTITUTE  (3INDBHU,3INDBDA,3INDTRM,3RUMBUC)
           (3INDIND) Mizoram University, Tanhril, Aizawl
           (3CZRCZR) Brno University of Technology, Brno, Czech
            Republic
REFERENCE  (J,EPJ/P,140,38,2025)
FACILITY   (VDGT,3INDTRM) Folded Tandem Ion Accelerator
INC-SOURCE (P-LI7) Protons (Ep=3.6, 4.6, 5.0 MeV, with an energy
            spread 0.02 MeV.
SAMPLE     (51-SB-121,ENR=0.5721) target has a density of
            6.697 g/cm3, with masses of 0.3502 g at 3.6 MeV,
            0.3648 g at 4.6 MeV, and 0.3690 g at 5.0 MeV.
           (49-IN-115,ENR=0.9571) target has a density of
            7.310 g/cm3, with masses of 0.0794 g at 3.6 MeV,
            0.1024 g at 4.6 MeV, and 0.0996 g at 5.0 MeV.
DETECTOR   (HPGE)
METHOD     (ACTIV) The Sb samples were cooled for 1-1.5 hr and
            counted for 2 hr, while the In foils were cooled for
            25-45 min and counted for 10-30 min.
CORRECTION Corrected for
           -Low energy 7Li(p,n1)7Be neutron background,
           -gamma-ray self-attenuation.
ERR-ANALYS (ERR-T) Total uncertainties are due to:
           (MONIT-ERR) Standard cross section, In
           (ERR-1) Photo peak count, Sb
           (ERR-2) Photo peak count, In
           (ERR-3) Gamma-ray intensity, Sb
           (ERR-4) Gamma-ray intensity, In
           (ERR-5) Number of atoms, Sb
           (ERR-6) Number of atoms, In
           (ERR-7) Isotopic abundance, Sb
           (ERR-8) Isotopic abundance, In
           (ERR-9) efficiency ratio
           (ERR-10) Time factor, Sb
           (ERR-11) Time factor, In
